COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 585, L.D. 1444
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment clarifies that a subsequent foreclosure action may be based only upon
33 a default of the mortgage that occurred after the entry of foreclosure judgment in favor of
44 the mortgagor and may not seek recovery of any sums due prior to the entry of the
55 foreclosure judgment. The amendment also clarifies the retroactive application of the
66 provisions of the bill. Finally, the amendment directs the judicial branch to adopt rules
77 implementing the changes to the foreclosure process.
